                     <handNote xml:id="h1" script="Ethiopic">
                        <ab type="script">Hand a: mediocre; hand b: mediocre; hand c: rather fine; hand d: rather fine.</ab>
                        <seg type="ink">Black, red (strong vermilion: fols. 3ra-37vb, 69va-70ra; vivid vermilion: fols. 39rb-42vb; strong amaranth: fols. 38ra-57v)</seg>
                        <persName role="scribe" corresp="PRS00000">Yämanä Bǝrhan</persName>The scribe’s signature (s. Additio 2) mentions Yämanä Bǝrhan as the scribe of the text on fols. 3ra-39ra l.17 (hand a).<date>19th cent.</date>
                        <list type="abbreviations">
                           <item>Some of the abbreviations used throughout the text:</item>
                           <item>ም፡/ምል፡/ምልጣ፡ for ምልጣን፡</item>
                           <item>ማኅ፡ for ማኅሌት፡</item>
                           <item>ሰላ፡ for ሰላም፡</item>
                           <item>አም፡/ዘአምላ፡ for ዘአምላኪየ፡</item>
                           <item>ይት፡/ይትባ፡ for ይትባረክ፡</item>
                           <item>አቡ፡ for አቡን፡</item>
                           <item>እስ፡ for እስመ፡ ለዓለም፡</item>
                           <item>በዜ፡ for በዜማ፡</item>
                           <item>አራ፡/አራራ፡ for አራራይ፡</item>
